  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing and Sustainability Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and execute social media strategies aligned with the company’s business objectives.</li><li>Develop and implement digital, social media, and offline marketing campaign plans, including content creation (photos, reels, videos, graphics, etc.) for various platforms.</li><li>Plan and execute outreach activities and events (schools and community) to support sustainability and marketing initiatives.</li><li>Monitor and analyse campaign performance using relevant metrics and prepare performance reports with insights and recommendations.</li><li>Conduct market research to evaluate trends, digital performance, SEO rankings, brand awareness, and competitive activities.</li><li>Support SEO efforts—including keyword research, on-page optimisation, content recommendations, and performance monitoring.</li><li>Manage advertising and promotional activities, collaborations, and partnerships.</li><li>Support the growth, engagement, and optimisation of all digital platforms.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Marketing, Communications, Business, or a related field.</li><li>Fresh grads are welcome! Up to 2 years’ experience in digital/social media marketing is a bonus.</li><li>You understand the basics of digital marketing (or you’re eager to learn!).</li><li>Creative, curious, but also most importantly organized and responsible.</li><li>A self-starter who loves working with a team but can perform solo too.</li><li>Passion for content, branding, and making a positive impact.</li><li>Okay with occasional weekend event duties — we promise they’re fun!</li></ul>",
